time required: 20 minutes
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Lower the heat to medium.

Once the rice is cooked, stir it into the pork with the @chicken stock paste{15%g}, @korma curry paste{50%g} and @peas{120%g} until well combined.

Stir the @mango chutney{40%g} through your pilaf.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

When ready, share the pork pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} to finish.

Enjoy!